      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The amino acid threonine, (2<i>S</i>,3<i>R</i>)-2-amino-3-hydroxybutanoic acid, has two chirality centers.</p>\n<p><b>(a)</b> Draw threonine, using normal, wedged, and dashed lines to show dimensionality.</p>\n<p><b>(b)</b> Draw a diastereomer of threonine, and label its chirality centers as <i>R</i> or <i>S</i>.</p>\n",
